---
const tagline = "Trajectory prediction RMSE −64%. VRU detection 99.7% under aerial occlusion. Hard-case success +50% with curated training. Aerial drone data is the highest-leverage missing input in AV model performance — and AV teams can't capture it themselves at scale.";
const subline = "Skydock delivers on-demand, US-coverage, OpenSCENARIO 2.0-formatted aerial captures that fill the trajectory, prediction, and validation gaps in your training pipelines.";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/favicon.svg`} />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
    <meta name="description" content={tagline} />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Skydock — Aerial BEV scenarios for AV training" />
    <meta property="og:description" content={tagline} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <title>Skydock — Aerial BEV scenarios for AV training</title>
    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --bg: #0a0e1a;
        --bg-elev: #111827;
        --border: #1f2937;
        --text: #e5e7eb;
        --text-dim: #9ca3af;
        --text-strong: #f9fafb;
        --accent: #60a5fa;
        --accent-dim: #1e3a8a;
        --accent-soft: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.08);
        --good: #9ee37d;
        --warn: #e5b85a;
        --mono: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Cascadia Code', 'Roboto Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
        --sans: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
      body {
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        font-family: var(--sans);
        line-height: 1.65;
        font-size: 17px;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;
      }
      a {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
        transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
      }
      a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--accent); }
      .container {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 24px;
      }
      header.site-header {
        padding: 24px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        background: var(--bg);
        z-index: 10;
      }
      .site-header .row {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
      }
      .brand {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 18px;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .brand::before {
        content: '◆ ';
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      .nav {
        display: flex;
        gap: 24px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
      }
      .nav a {
        color: var(--text-dim);
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      .nav a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .nav { display: none; }
      }
      section.hero { padding: 96px 0 56px; }
      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 60px);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.05;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin-bottom: 28px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .hero p.tagline {
        font-size: 22px;
        color: var(--text);
        max-width: 680px;
        margin-bottom: 22px;
        line-height: 1.4;
      }
      .hero p.subline {
        font-size: 17px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        max-width: 680px;
      }
      .hero-meta {
        margin-top: 32px;
        display: flex;
        gap: 28px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
      .hero-meta .label { color: var(--accent); margin-right: 8px; }
      section {
        padding: 64px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      h2 {
        font-size: 13px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 24px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 26px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        line-height: 1.3;
      }
      h4 {
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      p { margin-bottom: 18px; color: var(--text); }
      p.dim { color: var(--text-dim); }
      strong { color: var(--text-strong); font-weight: 600; }

      blockquote.pullquote {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
        padding: 12px 0 12px 24px;
        margin: 28px 0;
        font-size: 19px;
        color: var(--text);
        font-style: italic;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }
      blockquote.pullquote .attribution {
        display: block;
        margin-top: 10px;
        font-style: normal;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      }

      .sim-frame {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 14px;
        margin: 28px 0;
      }
      .sim-frame img {
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      .sim-caption {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        margin-top: 12px;
        padding-top: 12px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      }

      ul.feature-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      ul.feature-list li {
        padding: 14px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        display: flex;
        gap: 18px;
        align-items: baseline;
      }
      ul.feature-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.feature-list .key {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--accent);
        min-width: 170px;
        flex-shrink: 0;
      }
      ul.feature-list .val { color: var(--text); }

      .stat-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
        gap: 16px;
        margin: 28px 0;
      }
      .stat {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 22px 20px;
      }
      .stat .value {
        font-size: 26px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--text-strong);
        line-height: 1;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      }
      .stat .label {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
      }
      .stat .footnote {
        margin-top: 8px;
        font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-family: var(--mono);
      }

      table.compare {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      table.compare th,
      table.compare td {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 12px 12px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        vertical-align: top;
      }
      table.compare th {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 500;
        background: var(--accent-soft);
      }
      table.compare td.headline {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--text-strong);
        white-space: nowrap;
      }
      table.compare tr.skydock-row {
        background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.06);
      }
      table.compare tr.skydock-row td.headline { color: var(--accent); }

      table.pricing {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-size: 15px;
      }
      table.pricing th,
      table.pricing td {
        text-align: left;
        padding: 14px 16px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      table.pricing th {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 11px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      table.pricing td.tier {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      table.pricing td.price {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 600;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .deliverable-card {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 22px;
        margin: 24px 0;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13.5px;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      .deliverable-card .tree-line { color: var(--text-dim); }
      .deliverable-card .file { color: var(--accent); }
      .deliverable-card .desc { color: var(--text-dim); }

      .scene-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
        gap: 12px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .scene-tag {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 12px 14px;
      }
      .scene-tag .name {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .scene-tag .desc {
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        line-height: 1.4;
      }

      ul.faq-list {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      ul.faq-list li {
        padding: 18px 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      ul.faq-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .faq-q {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 14px;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        font-weight: 500;
      }
      .faq-a {
        color: var(--text);
        font-size: 16px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      ul.sla-list { list-style: none; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
      ul.sla-list li {
        padding: 10px 0 10px 30px;
        position: relative;
        color: var(--text);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }
      ul.sla-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.sla-list li::before {
        content: "✓";
        position: absolute;
        left: 0;
        top: 10px;
        color: var(--good);
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      ul.sla-list .pct {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        color: var(--accent);
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .contact-card {
        background: var(--bg-elev);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 30px;
        margin: 24px 0;
      }
      .contact-card .name {
        font-size: 22px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
        color: var(--text-strong);
      }
      .contact-card .role {
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 13px;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        margin-bottom: 18px;
      }
      .contact-card .bio { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-dim); margin-bottom: 22px; }
      .contact-links { display: flex; gap: 24px; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 14px; }

      .cta-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 14px;
        margin-top: 28px;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
      }
      .cta {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 14px 22px;
        border-radius: 6px;
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 500;
        border-bottom: none;
      }
      .cta.primary { background: var(--accent); color: #0a0e1a; }
      .cta.primary:hover { background: #7ab1f5; border-bottom: none; }
      .cta.secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--accent);
        border: 1px solid var(--accent);
      }
      .cta.secondary:hover {
        background: var(--accent-soft);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
      }

      footer {
        padding: 48px 0;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        text-align: center;
        color: var(--text-dim);
        font-family: var(--mono);
        font-size: 12px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        body { font-size: 16px; }
        section.hero { padding: 64px 0 40px; }
        ul.feature-list li { flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
        ul.feature-list .key { min-width: 0; }
        table.compare, table.pricing { font-size: 13px; }
        table.compare th, table.compare td,
        table.pricing th, table.pricing td { padding: 10px 8px; }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="container row">
        <span class="brand">skydock</span>
        <nav class="nav">
          <a href="#scenario">What you get</a>
          <a href="#capture">How it works</a>
          <a href="#problem">Problem</a>
          <a href="#evidence">Evidence</a>
          <a href="#scenario">What you get</a>
          <a href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
          <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
          <a href="#pilot">Start a pilot</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="container">
          <h1>Move your AV models past the long tail.</h1>
          <p class="tagline">{tagline}</p>
          <p class="subline">{subline}</p>
          <div class="hero-meta">
            <span><span class="label">delivery</span>4 hr SLA</span>
            <span><span class="label">format</span>OpenSCENARIO 2.0</span>
            <span><span class="label">starting</span>$339/scenario</span>
            <span><span class="label">pilot</span>from 100 scenarios</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="problem">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The problem</h2>
          <h3>Three places AV teams are stuck on model performance.</h3>
          <p>
            Modern AV models &mdash; whether modular (perception → prediction → planning)
            or end-to-end foundation models &mdash; are bottlenecked on the same
            kinds of data. The long tail of behaviors, the rare edge cases, the
            multi-agent interactions captured from above without ego-vehicle
            occlusion. These aren't problems of more data; they're problems of
            the <em>right</em> data, in formats that drop into existing pipelines.
          </p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
              <span class="key">trajectory prediction</span>
              <span class="val">Plateaus on ego-perspective data because behaviors that matter most for safety happen between agents that don't share a viewpoint. Models trained on aerial drone trajectories (highD, inD, openDD) reliably outperform same-architecture models trained on ego data.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">perception validation</span>
              <span class="val">Requires ground truth from a sensor system independent of the one being validated. Internal capture has correlated errors with the model being tested. Aerial drone capture provides the structural independence the safety case needs.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">hard-case coverage</span>
              <span class="val">The scenario library that gates the safety case grows linearly with new requirements &mdash; but the hardest scenarios (unprotected lefts, VRU interactions, school zones at dismissal) are the slowest to capture organically and the highest-leverage to add.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="evidence">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>The evidence</h2>
          <h3>What the published research says about aerial drone data.</h3>
          <p>
            Aerial drone data is the demonstrated training source for the
            largest published improvements in AV model performance. The data
            quality &mdash; 25Hz sampling, unoccluded multi-agent visibility,
            full intersection in a single frame &mdash; is structurally
            unavailable from ego-vehicle sensors.
          </p>
          <div class="stat-grid">
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">−64%</div>
              <div class="label">trajectory prediction RMSE</div>
              <div class="footnote">EPN model on highD vs SOTA</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">+50%</div>
              <div class="label">hard-case success rate</div>
              <div class="footnote">RoboTron-Sim curated training, ICCV 2025</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">−67%</div>
              <div class="label">collision rate in simulation</div>
              <div class="footnote">curated long-tail training, 16%→5.5%</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">99.7%</div>
              <div class="label">aerial pedestrian detection</div>
              <div class="footnote">CNN, vs 30-50% ego under occlusion</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">18-72%</div>
              <div class="label">trajectory accuracy range</div>
              <div class="footnote">Velocity Vector Field on highD</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">+6.8 mAP</div>
              <div class="label">person detection</div>
              <div class="footnote">aerial + ego multi-dataset training</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="dim">
            <strong>Honest caveat:</strong> these results are for aerial drone
            data in general &mdash; the published highD, inD, openDD, RoboTron-Sim
            studies. Skydock-specific evidence comes from your paid pilot:
            we deliver 100 scenarios in your target area, you measure
            improvement on your benchmarks, we publish jointly subject to your
            IP terms. The structural argument for why aerial data should work
            doesn't depend on Skydock; the customer-specific magnitude does.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="why">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Why this is hard to solve internally</h2>
          <h3>The existing alternatives, and why they don't fill the gap.</h3>
          <p>
            If aerial drone data is this valuable, why hasn't every AV
            company already captured it themselves? Because the operational
            economics don't work for any single customer &mdash; and the
            existing third-party options solve the wrong subset of the
            problem.
          </p>
          <table class="compare">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Approach</th>
                <th>Limitation</th>
                <th>Per-scenario cost</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="headline">Internal drone team</td>
                <td>Capacity caps at 2-4 captures/day per crew. 7 of 8 AV companies we surveyed tried this and stopped within a year &mdash; operational overhead, FAA Part 107 compliance, and dedicated drone-ops engineering pulls senior eng off core work.</td>
                <td>$1,000+</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="headline">levelXdata (highD/inD/rounD)</td>
                <td>Established 7-year commercial aerial datasets. German highways/intersections/roundabouts only. Fixed-location captures, no on-demand custom waypoints, custom format requires conversion.</td>
                <td>commercial license</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="headline">Academic datasets</td>
                <td>openDD, MiTra, DeepUrban, AUTOMATUM &mdash; fixed snapshots from one-time research collections. Free for research, commercial use restricted. No SLA.</td>
                <td>free, research-grade</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="headline">Fixed-base drone box</td>
                <td>One location per install. Designed for industrial inspection, not road scenarios.</td>
                <td>$15K+ install</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="headline">Synthetic BEV</td>
                <td>Strong on volume, weaker on edge-case fidelity. Used <em>alongside</em> real data by every customer we spoke to, not as a substitute.</td>
                <td>$50 - $300</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="skydock-row">
                <td class="headline">Skydock</td>
                <td>US-geography vehicle-deployed autonomous capture. On-demand custom waypoints, OpenSCENARIO 2.0 native, commercial SLA. Multi-tenant corpus amortizes operational cost across customers.</td>
                <td>$100 - $339</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <h4 style="margin-top: 32px; margin-bottom: 14px;">The cost math, for context</h4>
          <p class="dim">
            For a customer building 500 scenarios internally vs buying from
            Skydock at the volume tier:
          </p>
          <div class="stat-grid">
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">$100K</div>
              <div class="label">Skydock (500 × $200)</div>
              <div class="footnote">delivered in ~1.5 months</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">$382K</div>
              <div class="label">internal program build</div>
              <div class="footnote">8 months to first 500 delivered</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">$500K</div>
              <div class="label">commercial drone services</div>
              <div class="footnote">$1K/scenario industry rate</div>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="value">−74%</div>
              <div class="label">cost vs internal</div>
              <div class="footnote">plus 4-6 months time-to-value</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="dim">
            Cost-to-replicate inputs: AV engineer loaded labor ($100-170/hr),
            commercial drone service rates ($200-500/hr industry standard,
            $1K/scenario typical full delivery), annotation labor
            ($30-150/scenario for 3D agent cuboids), drone + vehicle + dock
            capex amortization. Sources: Glassdoor AV salary data, UAV Coach
            commercial drone pricing, BasicAI 2025 annotation cost guide.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="scenario">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>What you get</h2>
          <h3>A scenario package that drops into your pipeline.</h3>
          <p>
            Every Skydock scenario is a 30-120 second aerial bird's-eye-view
            recording captured from 80m AGL, delivered as a four-file package
            named by scenario ID. No proprietary schemas, no custom ingestion.
          </p>
          <div class="deliverable-card">
            <span class="tree-line">scenario_skydock-mission-00042/</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">metadata.json</span>           <span class="desc">scene class · GPS with uncertainty · capture geometry · DJI Mini 4 Pro calibration · quality score with methodology</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">agent_tracks.json</span>       <span class="desc">per-frame ENU positions of every visible vehicle / pedestrian / cyclist at 30 fps, with heading and speed</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">├─</span> <span class="file">scenario.xosc</span>           <span class="desc">OpenSCENARIO 2.0 export — road network reference, scenario entities, storyboard skeleton</span><br>
            <span class="tree-line">└─</span> <span class="file">raw_video.mp4</span>           <span class="desc">optional 4K H.265 source video — request at scenario commission time</span>
          </div>
          <p class="dim">
            File sizes: metadata ~2 KB · agent_tracks 50-500 KB depending on
            agent count · OpenSCENARIO ~5 KB · raw 4K video 200-600 MB.
            Sample package available on request.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="capture">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>How it works</h2>
          <h3>Vehicle arrives at waypoint → drone captures → package delivered in 4 hours.</h3>
          <p>
            When a Skydock-equipped vehicle reaches a pre-planned waypoint, or
            the operator triggers manually, the system runs a 2-second pre-flight
            check, deploys a sub-250g drone, climbs to 80m AGL, captures, and
            returns. Total mission time: ~90 seconds. The vehicle is stationary
            throughout per FAA Part 107 VLOS.
          </p>
          <ul class="feature-list">
            <li>
              <span class="key">trigger</span>
              <span class="val">Pre-planned waypoint, operator manual button, or hard-brake event. Custom waypoints (specific intersections, times of day, conditions) can be added to the operator's route.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">capture geometry</span>
              <span class="val">80m AGL · 80° diagonal FOV · ~67m footprint radius — captures a full signalized intersection or a 130m corridor in a single frame.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">capture duration</span>
              <span class="val">30-120s per scenario, operator-configurable. Default 60s for intersection scenarios, 30s for crosswalks, 120s for arterial corridors.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">processing</span>
              <span class="val">Cloud pipeline: upload → BEV transform → YOLOv8 + ByteTrack agent detection → OpenSCENARIO export → quality scoring → delivery.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">delivery</span>
              <span class="val">S3 pre-signed URL within 4 hours of capture. Optional SFTP, custom S3 bucket, or streaming API endpoint for enterprise customers.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

