            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">trajectory prediction</span>
              <span class="val">Train trajectory and behavior-prediction models on naturalistic agent interactions captured from above. Same use case as highD/inD/openDD, but with on-demand US coverage and custom waypoints.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="key">perception validation</span>
              <span class="val">Validate your on-vehicle perception against ground truth captured by a fully independent sensor system. The independence is the point — same-stack validation has correlated errors.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="dim">
            <strong>What we're not built for:</strong> training ego-vehicle
            perception models directly. Perception models need to learn
            from sensor data in the perspective they're deployed in
            (ego-vehicle cameras + lidar). Aerial BEV is the complement to
            that training data, not a replacement for it. If you're looking
            for ego-perspective camera/lidar capture, talk to a different
            vendor &mdash; we'll happily refer.
          </p>
        </div>
